summary:
My name is Thyra SM van Veen, MA and I followed my Bachelor's on the subject Celtic Languages and Culture at Utrecht University. My interests lie in languages, mythology and history. I have always dreamed about doing a job that involves working with languages, learning languages, and writing on historical and mythological subjects. Researching, questioning and then writing down my ideas and findings, analysing points and facts: it is something that has always interested me. It is also the reason why I decided to follow the Master's Ancient, Medieval and Renaissance Studies.  

I have done volunteer work: helping to arrange a charity walk, working at a Dutch school in Cambridge for children, to name two examples. I am willing to start a new working experience.

I am fluent in English, Dutch, German (writing is still an issue) and have retained a degree of Spanish. I have knowledge of the Modern Celtic Languages: Scottish Gaelic, Welsh, Breton and Irish Gaelic regarding their vitality. I am only able to converse in Welsh.
treasury_media: [{'url': None, 'title': 'Continental Celtic Heritage (Final).doc', 'description': 'During the Celtomania of the Early Modern period, past countries who had Celtic peoples living in them began venerating their past Celtic heroes. I wanted to know the extent the archaeological finds are part of the heritage of these countries, and the political and personal reasons why they would be considered as part of the heritage. In this essay, I focused on France and Spain.', 'image': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C4D2DAQG1Yb20ErPOCw/profile-treasury-document-cover-images_1920/0/1620639710792?e=1692892800&v=beta&t=bHmaRbIiWO_op8cavWnVpwW-MNvJTf_cyWl4lPjQjQM'}, {'url': None, 'title': '(Final) Essay - Subversion of the Index Librorum Prohibitorum.doc', 'description': 'This was the essay wrote as part of my final exam for the course History of the Early Modern book. I explored the methods that authors on the Index Librorum Prohibitorum and the printers took in order to subvert the Index and still get the works published. I thoroughly enjoyed researching and writing this paper!', 'image': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C4D2DAQE-wL2h_pdn6w/profile-treasury-document-cover-images_1920/0/1620141456110?e=1692892800&v=beta&t=YQLbpNAp7UCv1103_vZHiGeXnqMu72ceBRdcqK3epsk'}, {'url': None, 'title': 'Margarita (final).pdf', 'description': "I always found pet graves fascinating; it goes to show that our love for our furry friends is not dictated by time or space, but us as humans. I wanted to explore in this essay whether it was possible to discern the status of this poor dog's owners through a study of the epigraphical evidence and the grave stone itself. ", 'image': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C4D2DAQGVx1jNcoOOEA/profile-treasury-document-cover-images_1920/0/1619638663495?e=1692892800&v=beta&t=I1dH1d6P24UNrA3K46Zw-DnXAZGL5TLpzS32oCv2hLk'}, {'url': None, 'title': 'To what extent did status (Final).docx', 'description': 'This essay was part of my Master\'s course Medieval Law. I found the subject of the twelve men and women exempt from the concept of "sick maintenance" (a rudimentary health care system that existed in Ireland pre 650 CE). These men and women were only permitted to have a "nursing fee", and I wanted to explore to what extent did their status, gender and occupation dictated the amount of this fee. ', 'image': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C4D2DAQFLFha_nsofIw/profile-treasury-document-cover-images_1920/0/1619638479146?e=1692892800&v=beta&t=O_3otioFyiJmYdzBv7i2CJKbpLFoLAqfKOxzHD2N968'}, {'url': None, 'title': '(Final) Essay Cultural Evolution of Monsters.doc', 'description': 'Once more, I picked a werewolf subject: I studied the cultural memory influences on the changes between Ancient werewolves, Bisclavret, Alphonse and three modern examples of the werewolf: Remus Lupin, of the Harry Potter series written by JK Rowling, Grishmak Blood Drinker and the Werewolves in the Cry of the Icemark and the werewolves as shown in the teleseries Teen Wolf. I realised soon I may need more words for this study if I wish to continue it in the future!', 'image': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C4D2DAQF2aJbKmpR31A/profile-treasury-document-cover-images_1920/0/1619638336368?e=1692892800&v=beta&t=sCtrWongTeJYT3fH-GWRdoFu-3v77NwOQL5hDNqbH8c'}, {'url': None, 'title': 'The Case of Jean Coustain final (1).pdf', 'description': "I decided to play a Medieval Sherlock Holmes: I investigated the motive, means and opportunity a Court servant known as Jean Coustain was accused and found guilty of the attempted poisoning of his liege lord. It was possibly one of the most fun and infuriating essays I had ever written: the role of Necromancy and witch hunts during this time came into play. One of Coustain's alleged accomplices was a female necromancer who was never tried nor arrested. This was definitely not elementary!  ", 'image': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C4D2DAQERqL9-S3tqcw/profile-treasury-document-cover-images_1920/0/1619637798677?e=1692892800&v=beta&t=xRvXw4f0VNuh6gdHXWS_JzKSshxVoHBzDo5Gdt9vLTY'}, {'url': None, 'title': 'Thanatos essay (v4) (4).pdf', 'description': 'I have always held a fascination and deep-seated attachment to the gods of Greek mythology. One of those said gods that has always intrigued me is the god of death Thanatos, the son of Nyx and Erebus, twin to Hypnos the god of Sleep. In this essay I explored the evolution of the visual and literary perception of Thanatos and death: how he went from deity to Grim Reaper. I still feel very passionate about this piece of work ', 'image': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C4D2DAQEND6eXzpV-MQ/profile-treasury-document-cover-images_1920/0/1619637689120?e=1692892800&v=beta&t=1-waMGY3QfMHm5Ph5AGt4zAkG6J7Rpa-OvA1B4p69DA'}, {'url': None, 'title': 'Creative Writing Portfolio (Final) - van Veen.docx', 'description': "This is the portfolio I compiled during my Creative Writing course in my third year of my Bachelor's. My writing style is mostly fantasy based, but I also tried my hand at a Steampunk story at some point, which was a new experience for me and the teacher, since I was amongst the first to try that in his course. This piece also features a scene between characters of a story I am writing, Nimueh and Gwenllian, and the portfolio piece is the basis of a small novella.", 'image': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C4D2DAQHgD5FZ9cD_3A/profile-treasury-document-cover-images_1920/0/1619637396110?e=1692892800&v=beta&t=U8QN9A_Xo1lgkaWJIQYgApARqnyqtyxypF_x--OiXn8'}]
